<br>
There are several single spawns away from the main tree area (don't pull from that untill you are well used to the area - you'll get more than one and at 44 you cant take 2 at once) - Most are along the shore edge - there is really only one wanderer to watch out for. Sit there for a while to see his whole pathing route, then pick him off, then a single spawn (the 1 bird tree hut located at shore edge right close to stone hillside), then wanderer again, etc<br>
<br>
The higher level you get, the more you can do in a cycle - I started off killing wanderer, medding etc, then few mins later killing the single spawn, then medding till wanderer popped again.<br>
<br>
Started at 45, by 51 I was killing a cycle of 5 of them. There are 3 types of birds (well 4 of them but you wont see the Warriors in that spot) Lightfoots (easiest ones) and 2 other ones - bah cant remember the mob names - the toughest one is still blue at 51, but doesnt spawn as often as the other 2 types, who were all light blue by then (do level 50 here - theres enough blues to make it worth your time)<br>
<br>
K rambling now :P<br>
<br>
